AEtate jam affectum, “Already advanced in years,'' lit. “affected with age.” 7. Ea: iis coloniis quas Sulla, dte. The dictator Sulla had rewarded his soldiers by establishing whole legions in Italian towns, such as Faesulae‚ Capua, and others, whose citizens were obliged to give up their property to the soldiers. These were the military colonies of Sulla, of which there were twenty-three. The soldiers, who thus became suddenly rich, usually squandered their property in a very short time, and hence were anxious for another civil war in which to enrich themselves anew.
